# =============================================================================
# GitHub Actions Secrets Checklist
# =============================================================================
# Configure these secrets in: Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions
# =============================================================================

# REQUIRED SECRETS:
# ☐ GCP_PROJECT_ID
#    Your GCP project ID (e.g., "my-project-123456")

# ☐ GCP_SA_KEY
#    Service account JSON key file contents (entire file as string)
#    Create with: gcloud iam service-accounts keys create key.json --iam-account=...

# ☐ BIGQUERY_DATASET
#    BigQuery dataset name (default: "copo_do_mundo")

# ☐ BIGQUERY_TABLE
#    BigQuery table name (default: "votes")

# ☐ CLOUD_STORAGE_BUCKET
#    Cloud Storage bucket name (e.g., "my-project-copo-do-mundo-images")
#    Must be globally unique

# ☐ CLOUD_RUN_SERVICE_ACCOUNT
#    Service account email for Cloud Run
#    Format: "copo-do-mundo-sa@PROJECT_ID.iam.gserviceaccount.com"
#    Created by: ./infra/gcp-setup.sh

# ☐ ADMIN_PASSWORD
#    Admin password for the application

# OPTIONAL SECRETS (for Workload Identity Federation):
# ☐ WIF_PROVIDER
#    Workload Identity Provider (if using WIF instead of service account key)

# ☐ WIF_SERVICE_ACCOUNT
#    Service account for Workload Identity Federation

# =============================================================================
# Quick Setup:
# 1. Run: ./infra/gcp-setup.sh (creates GCP resources)
# 2. Add all secrets above in GitHub
# 3. Push to main branch to trigger deployment
# =============================================================================
